author: app.com
title: Thompson leads Ocean football to 26-12 win over 'Squan
text:
MORE OCEAN TOWNSHIP – Even when everyone knew Ocean senior running back Tyler Thompson was going to get the ball almost every down on Friday, he still couldn’t be stopped.
On a rainy and windy night, the Spartans handed the ball off to their star running back over and over, and he consistently delivered. Ocean’s star running back carried 29 time for a game-high 229 yards and a touchdown to lead the Spartans to a 26-12 non-divisional win at home over Manasquan.
“Tyler is the best running back in the Shore Conference,” said Ocean head coach Don Klein. “In a game like this, we were going to lean on him heavily and he made some big plays for us.”
The Spartans started the game with 26 unanswered points behind a strong first half from Thompson. On the Spartans’ first drive of the game, Thompson took a handoff 53 yards before being tackled at the 2-yard line. On the following play, junior quarterback Kenny Pickett took a keeper up the middle to put the Spartans up 6-0.
